title: Land's End
summary: Land's End[1] (Cornish: Penn an Wlas or Pedn an Wlas)[2] is a headland and tourist and holiday complex in western Cornwall, England, situated within the Penwith peninsula about eight miles (13Â km) west-south-west of Penzance at the western end of the A30 road. To the east of it is the English Channel, and to the west the Celtic Sea.
